{
  "id": "6226f9fe460518001d644a59",
  "title": "Drawing lines",
  "created": 1646721537,
  "updated": 1646723657,
  "lines": [
    {
      "id": "6226f9fe460518001d644a59",
      "text": "Drawing lines",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721537,
      "updated": 1646721541
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa06aff09e0000360c8e",
      "text": "By drawing lines, we can express the [relationships between distant objects].",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721542,
      "updated": 1646721698
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa1daff09e0000360cb3",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721566,
      "updated": 1646721566
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c91",
      "text": "Drawing lines is not included in the original [Kozane method]. Also, in the [KJ method], drawing lines is done after the spatial arrangement is completed.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721563
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c95",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c96",
      "text": "Why? Because [Kozane method]/[KJ method] are created in the age of pen and paper.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721568
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c99",
      "text": "Once you draw a line with a pen, you can't move objects on either end of the line. So you can't draw lines until everything is moved and the location is finalized.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646722205
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c9b",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721576
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c9d",
      "text": "Now [Kozaneba] the electronic software solved the problem.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721594
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c9e",
      "text": "You can draw a line between objects whose position has not yet been determined, and then move them again.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360c9f",
      "text": "Kozaneba surpassed the limits of the pen-and-paper methods. I feel it useful and do not want to go back to paper anymore.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360ca0",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360ca1",
      "text": "However, I am not sure it is beneficial to users who are not familiar with Kozane method/KJ method.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646722333
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360ca5",
      "text": "The function to draw lines gives the user more options. When there is a relationship between two objects, the user must choose whether to express the relationship by \"[putting them close together]\" or by \"[drawing a line between them].\" It increases the [burden] until users see benefit of Kozaneba.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721641
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360ca6",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360ca7",
      "text": "I have been doing the [Kozane method]/[KJ method] on paper for 10 years and has seen the benefits. In other words, drawing lines is not essential for the benefits.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721674
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360ca8",
      "text": "If you are wondering which is better between \"putting them close together\" and \"drawing a line between them\", you should better to put them close together.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360caa",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721688
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360cae",
      "text": "[* About the word \"line\"]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721719
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360caf",
      "text": "Lines are describing the [relationship between distant objects].",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721739
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360cb0",
      "text": "This \"distant objects\" is not necessarily only two things.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226fa15aff09e0000360cb1",
      "text": "I call the concept \"line\" because I haven't found a good word for it.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721557,
      "updated": 1646721557
    },
    {
      "id": "6226faaeaff09e0000360cb4",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721711,
      "updated": 1646721711
    },
    {
      "id": "6226faaeaff09e0000360cb5",
      "text": "[* Excerpt from [Release Notes]]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646721711,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868ad",
      "text": "　Arrows can now be added from the selection menu.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868ae",
      "text": "　 [https://gyazo.com/cef794096b06743c1bbd9b9c4b40f0c4]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868af",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b0",
      "text": "\tCreate an API for adding arrows.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b1",
      "text": "\t\tAdded the ability to draw arrows in bulk by user script.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b2",
      "text": "\t\t[https://gyazo.com/db24cc8fbda75c98c436458fb4fcf5fc]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b3",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b4",
      "text": "\tAdded double-headed arrows to the menu as I use them frequently.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b5",
      "text": "\t\tThe previous menu to add single-headed arrows also clearly states that its head is right.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b6",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b7",
      "text": "　The \"add arrow\" is now images, making it easier to see what will happen.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b8",
      "text": "　\t[https://gyazo.com/5b240c04a1f83c891eba3a279609964b]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868b9",
      "text": "　\tAdded the ability to draw arrows in batches with a user script\" on 2021-09-16.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868ba",
      "text": "　\tOn 2021-09-17, \"Add double-headed arrows to the menu since they are used frequently\" and \"Also, specify that the right side is the head in the menu for adding arrows\".",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868bb",
      "text": "　　These three changes were made to the menu in the image.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868bc",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868bd",
      "text": "\t[https://gyazo.com/8856cb7b7951c957dfdfe3cf6f27f15a]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868be",
      "text": "\t\tAdded the doubled line/arrow and the line without arrow heads",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868bf",
      "text": "\t\tIn previous version, the statement \"this and that are the same\" is only expressed by proximity. From current version, you can simply express it with doubled line.",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868c0",
      "text": " \t\t[https://gyazo.com/3ab0ab2660f69574e9bccef3e5481b2d]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868c1",
      "text": "　\"Leave from lines\" menu",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868c2",
      "text": " \tLeave from lines and arrow associations",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "622701afaff09e00005868c3",
      "text": "　　[https://gyazo.com/f83f83f555be85ab03d5b9d457b9ec98]",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723503,
      "updated": 1646723503
    },
    {
      "id": "62270222aff09e00005868c4",
      "text": "",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723619,
      "updated": 1646723619
    },
    {
      "id": "62270222aff09e00005868c5",
      "text": "---",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723619,
      "updated": 1646723623
    },
    {
      "id": "62270226aff09e00005868c7",
      "text": "You can add any comments and questions on the [forum https://scrapbox.io/kozaneba-forum/Drawing_lines].",
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e",
      "created": 1646723623,
      "updated": 1646723657
    },
